lib/grouping.py deduplicate_versions (lines 488-511):
```
for v in versions:
    is_duplicate = False
    # Check by ident (primary)
    ident = v.get('ident')
    if ident and ident != 'unknown':
        if ident in seen_idents:
            is_duplicate = True
        else:
            seen_idents.add(ident)          # <-- new distinct ident: is_duplicate stays False
    # Check by name+size (fallback)
    if not is_duplicate:                     # <-- gate True even after a successful distinct-ident insert
        name = v.get('name')
        size = v.get('size')
        if name and size:
            key = (name, size)
            if key in seen_name_size:
                is_duplicate = True          # <-- 2nd file dropped despite distinct valid ident
            else:
                seen_name_size.add(key)
    if not is_duplicate:
        result.append(v)
```
The name+size fallback runs whenever the ident did NOT collide (including when a NEW valid ident was just inserted), not only when ident is absent/unknown. `ident` is WebShare's unique per-file handle (it flows into `version['ident']` used for streaming/download and into grouped_movie_idents at lib/grouping.py:753), so two distinct idents are two genuinely distinct stored files.

