The clean_name() helper strips (among others) _RE_QUALITY=`\b(480p|720p|1080p|2160p|4K|UHD|FHD|HD)\b` (L40) and _RE_CODEC=`\b(x264|x265|...|AAC|AC3|DTS|DD5.1|Atmos|TrueHD)\b` (L42). A candidate consisting only of such a token cleans to '' (len<2), so cleaned_map stays empty and L405 returns the unmodified input verbatim.

Crucial mismatch with parsing.py: parsing's _PATTERN_QUALITY (L27) = `1080p|720p|2160p|4K|BluRay|WEB-DL|HDTV|WEBRip|BRRip` has NO bare `HD/UHD/FHD`, and its codec/audio patterns (L28-29) do not list standalone `AAC/AC3/DTS/Atmos/TrueHD`. So clean_series_name() KEEPS these tokens (non-empty canonical key) and get_display_name() (parsing.py L363-375) returns them as the display candidate — which the grouping picker then over-strips to empty and echoes back raw via L405.
